# clangd configuration for agent_native.
#
# This project intentionally exposes `agent/agent.hpp` as an umbrella header
# that re-exports every public submodule. Translation units typically include
# only that one header instead of enumerating sub-headers — that's the
# documented public API surface (see docs/architecture.md and bindings.md).
#
# clangd's include-cleaner is IWYU-style and doesn't know about this
# convention, so it flags the umbrella include as "unused" on every .cpp.
# It also flags common STL headers (`<iomanip>`, `<limits>`, `<numeric>`,
# `<sstream>`, …) as "unused" when symbols come transitively through
# `agent.hpp` — the same false-positive pattern.
#
# We disable the lint to keep IDE diagnostics aligned with the project's
# actual coding convention. Real compiler warnings (and clangd's other
# checks like type errors) are unaffected.

Diagnostics:
  UnusedIncludes: None
  MissingIncludes: None
